WEBVTT

00:07.179 --> 00:11.681
Previously on Day of The Dead.
[snarling and growling]

00:11.981 --> 00:13.471
Herb: They're eating our guests.

00:15.273 --> 00:16.140
Mom!

00:18.075 --> 00:18.776
[crunch sound]

00:21.178 --> 00:22.513
We have to get out of here.

00:26.951 --> 00:28.419
[snarling and growling]

00:34.325 --> 00:36.227
Come on! Let's go!

00:36.227 --> 00:38.029
Lauren: I parked out back!

00:38.029 --> 00:38.963
Herb: I know you.

00:38.963 --> 00:40.364
You're that junkie.

00:41.432 --> 00:43.234
You're a shitty excuse
for a doctor, you know that?

00:43.234 --> 00:44.101
Right there.

00:44.936 --> 00:45.803
Send out an EBS,
you text everyone,

00:46.337 --> 00:47.338
tell them go to the old Paymart.

00:48.139 --> 00:48.906
We could lock this place down,

00:49.774 --> 00:50.374
keep everybody safe
until help comes.

00:51.542 --> 00:54.845
She's playing around with
things she doesn't understand.

00:54.845 --> 00:57.181
Death is no longer the end.

00:57.181 --> 00:58.316
[snarling]

00:58.316 --> 01:01.519
[cries of pain]

01:01.519 --> 01:03.487
You ignorant prick.

01:21.072 --> 01:22.273
[panting]
It's okay.

01:23.140 --> 01:25.810
It's okay. We're going
to get you help.

01:33.150 --> 01:35.186
Herb: Can this jalopy
go any faster?

01:36.020 --> 01:36.887
You didn't wanna go to Paymart

01:36.887 --> 01:39.824
and now you're in a rush
to get there?

01:39.824 --> 01:41.225
Make up your mind, Herb.

01:41.225 --> 01:42.793
Well, forgive me for
feeling uncomfortable

01:42.793 --> 01:43.894
having my life
in your hands.

01:43.894 --> 01:45.296
You weren't complaining

01:46.330 --> 01:46.364
when I saved your ass
back at the country club.

01:46.897 --> 01:47.531
Both of you just stop.

01:47.531 --> 01:50.234
Please. Stop.

01:50.234 --> 01:52.103
This woman is a criminal.

01:52.103 --> 01:53.771
Herb: She almost cost me
my medical license!

01:53.771 --> 01:54.972
Jai: Herb, she told you
to stop!

01:54.972 --> 02:00.544
[phone vibrating]

02:00.544 --> 02:01.812
Oh my god, Mom.

02:02.913 --> 02:04.782
Please, please tell me you're
still stuck in Florida.

02:06.050 --> 02:08.252
No, Mom, please!
Stay there!

02:08.252 --> 02:09.954
Don't come here!

02:11.155 --> 02:13.124
No, I know I was pressuring
you to come

02:13.124 --> 02:14.492
but something terrible
has happened.

02:14.492 --> 02:16.460
Just where you are.

02:16.460 --> 02:18.362
No. The wedding's done.

02:18.362 --> 02:19.497
No, we didn't have it
without you.

02:19.497 --> 02:20.798
That's not what happened.

02:20.798 --> 02:21.832
Stop! Help!

02:21.832 --> 02:22.300
Stop!

02:22.300 --> 02:24.936
[tires screeching]

02:30.374 --> 02:31.442
Please help.

02:31.442 --> 02:35.413
My sister, we were out birding,
Mindy and I, when...

02:36.447 --> 02:38.249
Oh, Jesus!

02:38.249 --> 02:39.817
It hurts so bad.

02:39.817 --> 02:41.852
Alright. Mindy, just try
and relax, okay?

02:41.852 --> 02:42.286
[groans]

02:42.286 --> 02:43.387
I'm a doctor.

02:43.988 --> 02:44.989
How did this happen?

02:44.989 --> 02:46.190
Mindy heard something
in the bushes

02:46.190 --> 02:48.426
and then he was just there.

02:48.426 --> 02:50.428
It was so awful.

02:50.428 --> 02:52.964
We started to run
when we saw his... his...

02:52.964 --> 02:55.099
He had his thing out.

02:55.099 --> 02:56.400
His... his thing?

02:56.400 --> 02:57.435
You know what
I'm talking about.

02:58.502 --> 03:00.938
Those perverts and their things
they're so proud of.

03:00.938 --> 03:03.107
I tripped trying to get away.

03:03.107 --> 03:06.077
My god, I can still hear it
slapping against his thighs

03:06.077 --> 03:08.312
as he was chasing us.

03:08.312 --> 03:09.380
We have to get out of here.

03:09.380 --> 03:11.182
He's still out there.

03:11.182 --> 03:12.984
I can't do anything here.

03:12.984 --> 03:13.784
Amy!

03:14.919 --> 03:16.921
Get back in the damn car!

03:16.921 --> 03:18.356
What's going on?

03:18.356 --> 03:19.991
I have to get her to Paymart.

03:19.991 --> 03:21.759
Paymart?

03:21.759 --> 03:23.894
That place shut down.

03:23.894 --> 03:26.030
Didn't you guys get the alert?

03:26.030 --> 03:28.065
Okay, yeah, we'll be safe there.

03:28.065 --> 03:29.200
From the perverts?

03:29.200 --> 03:30.234
No, from the zomb‐

03:30.234 --> 03:31.102
Yes.

03:31.102 --> 03:32.503
Yes, the perverts.

03:32.503 --> 03:34.338
You'll be safe
from the perverts.

03:35.006 --> 03:36.007
There he is!

03:37.942 --> 03:39.977
[low growling]

03:41.912 --> 03:43.447
[moaning in pain]

03:47.952 --> 03:50.955
[snarling and growling]

03:52.823 --> 03:54.258
Ugh, really?

03:56.127 --> 03:58.095
Oh, my god.

03:58.095 --> 04:00.197
Holy shit.

04:00.197 --> 04:01.332
Zombie dick.

04:02.233 --> 04:04.502
Everybody in the car!

04:05.303 --> 04:07.805
Hey! Where are you going?

04:07.805 --> 04:08.506
Amy: Wait!

04:17.949 --> 04:21.819
[pulsing theme music]
♪

04:21.819 --> 04:36.467
♪

04:36.467 --> 04:41.005
♪

04:55.019 --> 04:55.820
[growling]
Oh, fuck!

04:56.454 --> 04:57.254
Shit!

04:57.254 --> 04:58.155
Hey! Forget about
the damn shoe!

04:58.155 --> 04:59.423
Mom and I bought
these shoes together.

04:59.423 --> 05:03.461
Now she's gone. I'm
not leaving the shoe!

05:03.961 --> 05:06.731
[screams]

05:08.099 --> 05:10.434
You sons of bitches!
You ruined everything!

05:10.434 --> 05:12.803
This was supposed to be
the happiest day of my life!

05:12.803 --> 05:14.772
[screams]

05:14.772 --> 05:16.107
She's losing it.

05:16.107 --> 05:19.877
[screams]

05:24.415 --> 05:26.450
[panting]

05:28.119 --> 05:30.888
Everybody I loved was in there!

05:30.888 --> 05:33.157
[sobbing]

05:37.261 --> 05:39.397
Amy: They're all dead now.

05:41.832 --> 05:44.101
Amy. Honey.

05:44.101 --> 05:45.770
All right, look.

05:45.770 --> 05:51.042
What happened sucks, and
I know... I know it sucks.

05:51.042 --> 05:52.209
[scoffs]

05:52.209 --> 05:53.244
But we're not safe here.

05:53.244 --> 05:54.045
Oh Jesus.

05:54.045 --> 05:56.213
Will you stop babying her?

05:56.213 --> 05:57.081
Hey, you.

05:57.081 --> 05:59.383
You listen to me.

05:59.383 --> 06:01.485
I am not gonna sit here
and die

06:01.485 --> 06:04.088
because you can't act
like an adult.

06:04.088 --> 06:07.091
Now, get up off your ass
and move!

06:11.896 --> 06:13.331
[exhales]

06:19.103 --> 06:20.037
There, you see?

06:20.037 --> 06:22.373
You just have to know
how to talk to her.

06:22.373 --> 06:23.908
[screams]

06:24.275 --> 06:25.042
Dad!

06:27.411 --> 06:31.315
Please, I... I just need
more time.

06:31.315 --> 06:35.086
I understand, but I've
discovered something.

06:35.086 --> 06:40.224
Some... something...
something miraculous.

06:40.224 --> 06:41.826
I don't care what you tell them,

06:41.826 --> 06:44.228
just don't let them do anything
without me.

06:44.228 --> 06:48.366
They've waited this long...
they can wait another 24 hours.

06:56.274 --> 06:58.276
You and I have work to do.

07:00.911 --> 07:05.950
♪

07:34.779 --> 07:38.082
All right, you boys know how
to use those?

07:38.082 --> 07:39.784
Good. Now, get out front.

07:39.784 --> 07:41.218
You keep an eye
on that parking lot.

07:44.155 --> 07:45.289
Paula?

07:47.024 --> 07:48.960
Are you crazy,
handing out guns?

07:48.960 --> 07:51.062
Someone's gonna get hurt.

07:51.062 --> 07:53.064
People are already
getting hurt.

07:53.064 --> 07:54.165
I'm giving them
a fighting chance.

07:54.165 --> 07:55.833
You can't just create
a militia.

07:55.833 --> 07:58.336
[laughs]
The hell I can't.

07:58.336 --> 08:00.237
Take a look at the second
amendment sometime.

08:00.237 --> 08:01.138
This isn't about politics.

08:02.139 --> 08:03.040
What's happening
out there is... is bigger

08:03.040 --> 08:04.775
than our election.

08:04.775 --> 08:05.910
[laughing]
Oh, ho, ho!

08:05.910 --> 08:08.779
Oh, that is really something
coming from you.

08:08.779 --> 08:12.350
You threatened to destroy my
family if I didn't step down.

08:12.350 --> 08:14.251
So you can kiss my ass.

08:14.251 --> 08:16.120
This town needs a leader
with a cool head,

08:16.120 --> 08:20.891
not one telling teenagers
to shoot on site.

08:20.891 --> 08:25.363
My husband Trey and I, we were
attacked by those creatures.

08:25.363 --> 08:29.066
My campaign manager
was brutally murdered,

08:29.066 --> 08:34.038
and my son, my only child,
was almost taken from us.

08:34.038 --> 08:36.240
Now, I will not stand by
and let a single member

08:36.240 --> 08:38.209
of this community
go through that.

08:38.209 --> 08:40.811
If we are going to survive
this day

08:40.811 --> 08:42.847
we need to stand together.

08:42.847 --> 08:44.849
We need to fight together!

08:51.555 --> 08:52.723
Luke, wait.

08:52.723 --> 08:53.391
Imagine how good her speech
would have been

08:53.391 --> 08:55.760
if I had actually died.

08:55.760 --> 08:57.228
I bet part of her wishes
that I did.

08:57.228 --> 08:58.362
Don't say that,
that's not fair.

08:58.362 --> 09:01.165
You know we're just props
to her, right?

09:01.165 --> 09:02.934
We're just supposed
to stand around and nod

09:02.934 --> 09:04.335
like a couple of assholes.

09:04.335 --> 09:07.471
You know, at least I stand up
to her every once in a while.

09:07.471 --> 09:09.240
What do you do?

09:09.240 --> 09:10.374
You just sneak around
screwing Nicole

09:10.374 --> 09:13.244
'cause you're too scared
to say anything.

09:13.244 --> 09:14.211
Luke.

09:14.211 --> 09:15.513
It's pathetic.

09:16.914 --> 09:18.816
You're pathetic.

09:28.926 --> 09:31.295
[growling and snarling]

09:31.295 --> 09:33.064
Dad, are you okay?

09:34.498 --> 09:36.801
[fighting grunts]

09:37.902 --> 09:38.970
Jai!

09:39.370 --> 09:41.939
Oh, you've gotta be kidding me.

09:43.541 --> 09:44.775
[gunshot]

09:48.446 --> 09:51.349
Y'all need a lift
to the Paymart?

09:52.984 --> 09:55.252
Bobby fucking Hart.

10:01.092 --> 10:06.931
♪

10:13.638 --> 10:14.905
♪
[drilling]

10:17.108 --> 10:18.109
[slam]

10:20.478 --> 10:23.180
I think I missed it.
Missed a stud or something.

10:27.451 --> 10:29.353
Hey, hey, Lauren!

10:29.353 --> 10:31.055
Oh, my god, I'm so glad
you're safe.

10:31.055 --> 10:32.356
And Jai and you guys.

10:32.356 --> 10:34.225
It's pretty bad out there, man.
Are you okay?

10:34.225 --> 10:35.526
Yeah.

10:35.526 --> 10:36.227
It's good to see you.

10:36.227 --> 10:37.862
You too, man.

10:38.396 --> 10:39.497
So?

10:41.799 --> 10:43.401
I was so worried about you.

10:43.401 --> 10:44.468
You were?

10:45.703 --> 10:49.373
I mean, I saved your ass this
morning so I'd be pretty pissed

10:49.373 --> 10:52.109
if you bit it the minute
I let you out of my sight.

10:52.109 --> 10:55.846
We kind of saved each other's
asses, but whatever.

10:55.846 --> 10:58.416
Well, I'm glad you're safe.

11:00.418 --> 11:01.986
You find your dad?

11:01.986 --> 11:02.820
No.

11:03.621 --> 11:04.255
He's probably passed
out somewhere,

11:05.056 --> 11:06.290
sleeping through
this whole thing.

11:06.290 --> 11:07.458
He'll turn up.

11:07.458 --> 11:09.760
In the meantime,
while you're here,

11:09.760 --> 11:12.897
why not check out Paymart's
extensive menswear department?

11:12.897 --> 11:14.498
Maybe you can ditch
the cargo shorts.

11:14.498 --> 11:16.467
Oh yeah?

11:16.467 --> 11:18.102
Lauren.

11:18.102 --> 11:19.904
Come on, we need help
in the infirmary.

11:19.904 --> 11:21.238
Why me?

11:22.373 --> 11:24.508
If you can sew up a corpse
you can suture a live person.

11:24.508 --> 11:25.843
Jai: Come on.

11:30.214 --> 11:33.050
Hell yeah, that's what
I'm talking about.

11:33.050 --> 11:35.219
Let's re‐kill these
undead fuckers.

11:35.219 --> 11:36.354
Bobby.

11:36.354 --> 11:37.822
Bobby Hart.

11:37.822 --> 11:40.524
You're Jerry's grandson,
aren't you?

11:40.524 --> 11:41.459
He was my Peepaw, yeah.

11:41.459 --> 11:45.496
I'm sorry to hear
he passed.

11:45.496 --> 11:47.265
He was a hell of a Peepaw.

11:47.265 --> 11:50.034
Listen, Bobby, before you
go out there blasting folks,

11:50.034 --> 11:53.037
I... I want you to think
about something.

11:53.037 --> 11:56.841
Your grandpa could be one
of those people out there.

11:56.841 --> 11:59.977
Nah, he's pinned to the floor
of the funeral home.

11:59.977 --> 12:02.980
Those things out there,
they used to be people.

12:02.980 --> 12:04.181
People we know.

12:05.216 --> 12:06.851
Our neighbors, our friends,
our... our Peepaws.

12:06.851 --> 12:09.120
We don't even know
what's causing this.

12:09.120 --> 12:11.389
What if there's a cure?
What if it's only temporary?

12:11.389 --> 12:14.225
We need to help them
and not destroy them.

12:14.225 --> 12:16.327
Are we the type of people

12:16.327 --> 12:19.997
who would slaughter their own
out of fear?

12:21.899 --> 12:27.505
You wouldn't shoot your poor old
Peepaw, Bobby, would you?

12:27.505 --> 12:30.074
Fuck no, I would not.

12:32.076 --> 12:33.110
[winces]

12:43.921 --> 12:46.123
That's some nice stitch work.

12:46.123 --> 12:47.458
Thanks.

12:48.859 --> 12:51.228
It's definitely weird doing this
on someone who's still alive.

12:51.228 --> 12:53.431
Because I'm not a doctor.

12:53.431 --> 12:55.232
I'd be way more comfortable
doing this on you

12:55.232 --> 12:57.201
if you were dead.

12:58.536 --> 12:59.837
No one's gonna die.

12:59.837 --> 13:01.973
You're fine.

13:01.973 --> 13:05.810
Lauren, why don't you uh,
go check on the next patient?

13:05.810 --> 13:07.244
Okay.

13:07.244 --> 13:10.081
Whatever you say, doc.

13:19.423 --> 13:21.092
[chuckles]

13:21.092 --> 13:21.993
What?

13:21.993 --> 13:27.331
I knew you were soft,
but uh... Christ.

13:27.331 --> 13:29.000
Lauren: No fucking way!

13:32.503 --> 13:34.238
You left us out there to die!

13:34.238 --> 13:36.540
[teary]
I'm sorry, I panicked.

13:36.540 --> 13:39.277
Please, you've gotta help
my sister.

13:39.844 --> 13:40.911
It's okay.

13:41.846 --> 13:44.949
Don't worry. Of course we'll
help you. Okay.

13:46.284 --> 13:46.817
[cries of pain]

13:46.817 --> 13:47.551
You're hurting her.

13:47.551 --> 13:49.487
I know. I'm sorry.

13:49.487 --> 13:50.488
I'm just trying to get
a better understanding

13:50.488 --> 13:52.857
of your sister's condition.

13:52.857 --> 13:54.825
Lauren, can you take her away
from here, please?

13:54.825 --> 13:56.093
I'm not leaving!

13:56.093 --> 13:58.496
Cindy, please, just...
just let him work.

13:58.496 --> 13:59.997
Come on.

14:03.000 --> 14:04.201
Go.

14:05.069 --> 14:06.470
[whimpering]

14:07.471 --> 14:10.107
I know you're in pain.

14:10.107 --> 14:12.343
But I'm gonna help you,
I promise.

14:15.813 --> 14:16.847
Jai.

14:18.950 --> 14:19.917
You do realize

14:19.917 --> 14:22.520
the only thing keeping her alive
is that stick.

14:22.520 --> 14:25.256
You try to remove it
she'll bleed out in 30 seconds.

14:25.256 --> 14:25.756
You don't know that.

14:25.756 --> 14:27.925
And neither do you!

14:27.925 --> 14:30.828
Not without an ultrasound.

14:30.828 --> 14:33.297
Now, I've been a physician
longer than you've been alive

14:33.297 --> 14:36.968
and I can tell a lost cause
when I see one.

14:36.968 --> 14:39.170
Now, you wanna help
this woman?

14:39.170 --> 14:43.307
Treat her pain and let her die
with dignity.

14:43.307 --> 14:48.245
Focus your efforts on people
you can actually save.

14:48.245 --> 14:50.548
Maybe you've been doing this job
too long.

14:50.548 --> 14:52.249
Our job is to save
every single patient,

14:52.249 --> 14:53.884
no matter how dire
the prognosis.

14:55.086 --> 14:59.290
Now, that doesn't make me soft,
it makes me a goddamn doctor.

15:06.864 --> 15:08.065
[clears throat]

15:09.133 --> 15:11.302
There used to be
a pharmacy here.

15:11.302 --> 15:14.839
See if you can find anything,
any kind of pain medication.

15:14.839 --> 15:17.108
Hydrocodone, Oxycontin,
anything strong.

15:17.108 --> 15:19.844
Even if it's expired.

15:19.844 --> 15:22.113
This woman is gonna need it.

15:22.113 --> 15:24.415
You want me to find
pain meds?

15:24.415 --> 15:27.251
What, you've got a problem
with that?

15:27.251 --> 15:31.455
Or do you want to trick Jai into
writing a prescription again?

15:31.455 --> 15:32.923
Kiss my ass.

15:39.697 --> 15:41.215
♪
[thwack]

15:46.290 --> 15:47.261
[thwack]

15:50.264 --> 15:51.232
[thwack]

15:53.367 --> 15:55.269
[thwack]

15:55.269 --> 15:57.137
Shopping?

15:57.137 --> 15:58.405
Oh, yeah.

15:58.405 --> 15:59.340
Lauren's always giving me
a hard time

15:59.340 --> 16:01.141
about my cargo shorts, so...

16:01.141 --> 16:02.409
Right.

16:03.477 --> 16:04.745
I don't really think the shorts
are the issue, man.

16:04.745 --> 16:06.380
[thwack]

16:06.380 --> 16:07.748
Whatever.

16:07.748 --> 16:09.717
Hey, this shit's crazy, right?

16:11.552 --> 16:13.487
Yeah. Yeah.

16:13.487 --> 16:15.456
Still not convinced it's not all
a bad dream.

16:15.456 --> 16:16.457
Yeah.

16:18.158 --> 16:20.194
Wanna take a cut at it?

16:22.396 --> 16:23.797
Yes or no?

16:26.200 --> 16:27.334
All right.

16:28.068 --> 16:29.270
All right.

16:33.540 --> 16:34.708
[thwack]

16:38.112 --> 16:39.146
[thwack]

16:42.383 --> 16:44.151
There you are.

16:45.319 --> 16:47.254
[sighs]

17:07.675 --> 17:08.509
Wow.

17:10.411 --> 17:13.347
I thought I was having
a bad day.

17:21.589 --> 17:24.592
Did the wedding even happen?

17:24.592 --> 17:27.528
What do you think?

17:27.528 --> 17:30.497
You know, you might have dodged
a bullet there.

17:30.497 --> 17:34.768
It's supposed to be the happiest
day of your life,

17:34.768 --> 17:38.372
but one day you're gonna wake up
and you're married to the mayor,

17:38.372 --> 17:41.108
your son hates you, and the guy
you were 22 years ago

17:41.108 --> 17:43.611
wouldn't give you the time
of day.

17:57.725 --> 17:59.660
[sighs]

17:59.660 --> 18:01.662
Something on your mind?

18:02.630 --> 18:05.733
Okay, let's see what
you remember.

18:06.533 --> 18:07.601
Hey.

18:08.269 --> 18:10.371
Hey, look.

18:10.371 --> 18:11.338
Look.

18:14.541 --> 18:17.544
Hey, what's this?

18:17.544 --> 18:19.747
What is this?

18:19.747 --> 18:21.448
[low growls]

18:24.518 --> 18:26.353
What about this?

18:27.187 --> 18:28.656
You know what this is?

18:28.656 --> 18:30.090
[grunts]

18:33.193 --> 18:34.595
[banging on bars]

18:34.595 --> 18:35.563
Dammit!

18:43.671 --> 18:44.705
What?

18:51.178 --> 18:52.212
Yes.

18:56.083 --> 18:57.084
That's yours.

18:59.086 --> 19:01.355
That's yours.

19:01.355 --> 19:03.324
[grunts]

19:24.211 --> 19:26.814
You remember!
You remember!

19:29.049 --> 19:32.086
Maybe you are in there
after all.

19:41.061 --> 19:43.097
I don't care about flooding
in Pittsburg!

19:43.097 --> 19:45.466
I need help here!

19:45.466 --> 19:47.401
This is a natural disaster!

19:47.401 --> 19:50.804
It's an unnatural disaster!

19:50.804 --> 19:52.773
I've got some boys armed
and headed out front

19:52.773 --> 19:53.540
to watch the perimeter,

19:54.341 --> 19:54.909
but they aren't exactly
Navy Seals.

19:55.476 --> 19:56.810
Any word on the backup?

19:56.810 --> 19:57.745
Goddammit.

19:57.745 --> 19:59.079
Assholes!

20:01.782 --> 20:04.118
National Guard's a no go.

20:05.152 --> 20:06.420
Oh Jesus.

20:08.188 --> 20:10.257
Then what're we gonna do?

20:10.257 --> 20:11.592
[explosion]

20:16.497 --> 20:17.598
Dig in.

20:17.598 --> 20:19.667
Make a stand here.

20:19.667 --> 20:22.303
Try to save as many people
as possible.

20:25.372 --> 20:28.075
Make sure your boys are locked
and loaded.

20:28.075 --> 20:29.710
I'll call the troopers again,

20:29.710 --> 20:32.513
try and see if I can light
a fire under their asses.

20:35.316 --> 20:36.350
Paula.

20:38.152 --> 20:40.187
Can I borrow your phone?

20:44.391 --> 20:45.426
[exhales]

20:51.265 --> 20:53.300
♪

21:40.648 --> 21:42.650
Looks like someone
beat me to it.

22:07.341 --> 22:08.742
Hey, assholes.

22:08.742 --> 22:11.412
I haven't seen you
in 90 days.

22:39.240 --> 22:41.242
...and then I lost it.
Cried like a baby
right in front of him.

22:41.242 --> 22:42.843
Luke was right.

22:42.843 --> 22:44.678
I am pathetic.

22:49.717 --> 22:52.186
[exhales]

22:52.186 --> 22:54.121
What about you?

22:54.121 --> 22:55.089
Huh?

22:55.089 --> 22:56.457
Trey, you just told me
your whole life story

22:56.457 --> 23:00.227
from everyone else's point
of view but yours.

23:00.227 --> 23:02.463
Paula did, Nicole said,
Luke told me...

23:02.463 --> 23:03.664
What about you?

23:03.664 --> 23:07.401
Where are you
in all of this?

23:07.401 --> 23:09.470
I don't know.

23:09.470 --> 23:12.139
I mean, Paula says‐

23:12.139 --> 23:14.408
I don't care what Paula says.

23:14.408 --> 23:15.709
What would you say

23:16.810 --> 23:18.646
if you didn't have all these
other voices in your head?

23:24.785 --> 23:26.420
I don't know.

23:29.189 --> 23:30.391
Well...

23:32.259 --> 23:33.694
If you ever met my dad,

23:33.694 --> 23:38.799
you'd know that I come from
some pretty controlling people.

23:38.799 --> 23:39.600
[chuckles]

23:42.436 --> 23:48.275
And a few years back I was
feeling so frustrated,

23:48.275 --> 23:49.543
so constricted, I...

23:49.543 --> 23:53.781
I felt like I couldn't
even breathe.

23:53.781 --> 23:55.516
You know what I did?

23:55.516 --> 23:57.785
I signed up for Krav Maga.

23:57.785 --> 23:59.386
What's that?

24:00.554 --> 24:03.190
You know, the Israeli art of
kicking the shit out of people?

24:03.190 --> 24:05.626
Okay, I know it's random

24:05.626 --> 24:11.131
but, I mean, just having
that little piece of control

24:11.131 --> 24:13.400
made me feel like I could start
taking the power back

24:13.400 --> 24:15.135
in the rest of my life.

24:15.135 --> 24:16.537
No shit.

24:16.537 --> 24:18.305
Yeah. No shit.

24:22.376 --> 24:23.744
Now probably isn't the best time

24:23.744 --> 24:25.813
to start martial arts classes,
is it?

24:25.813 --> 24:26.814
Yeah, well, that was my thing.

24:26.814 --> 24:29.183
You gotta find your own thing.

24:30.384 --> 24:33.654
And it doesn't need
to be a class.

24:33.654 --> 24:39.793
It can be a moment,
or a feeling.

24:39.793 --> 24:41.762
Anything that can be yours.

24:43.364 --> 24:46.600
And I promise you
when you find it,

24:46.600 --> 24:49.270
you'll be back in charge
of your own life.

24:54.241 --> 24:56.677
Jesus.

24:56.677 --> 24:58.812
I'm gonna do it.

25:00.681 --> 25:03.317
I'm gonna own my life!

25:03.317 --> 25:04.752
‐Thank you, Amy.
‐Yeah.

25:04.752 --> 25:06.153
That was...

25:06.820 --> 25:10.658
Oh...that was...

25:10.658 --> 25:11.625
Damn!

25:18.198 --> 25:21.602
Now all we gotta do is live
long enough for you to do it.

25:24.738 --> 25:26.640
What the hell is this?

25:26.640 --> 25:27.708
Why aren't you outside?

25:27.708 --> 25:29.243
I won't do it, Mayor.

25:29.243 --> 25:30.344
I ain't shooting my Peepaw.

25:30.344 --> 25:32.313
Not for you,
not for nobody.

25:32.313 --> 25:33.113
What the‐

25:33.881 --> 25:34.114
I had a little talk
with the boys.

25:35.082 --> 25:36.283
We've decided to take
a different approach.

25:37.251 --> 25:40.387
We are going to trap
those folks humanely.

25:40.387 --> 25:43.224
Are you shitting me?!

25:43.224 --> 25:45.059
You've seen what
those monsters can do!

25:45.059 --> 25:46.427
You're gonna get us
all killed!

25:46.427 --> 25:47.728
Well, that's your opinion.

25:47.728 --> 25:48.362
Hey! Hey!

25:48.362 --> 25:52.266
You listen to me, Parker!

25:52.266 --> 25:55.269
This election, it's not
happening, okay, not today.

25:55.269 --> 25:57.805
Now is not the time for some
sort of a power grab!

25:57.805 --> 25:59.173
This is life and death!

26:00.307 --> 26:00.608
And that's where we've always
differed, isn't it, Paula?

26:01.442 --> 26:02.376
You focus on death,
I focus on life.

26:02.376 --> 26:03.544
You see them as things,

26:03.544 --> 26:08.282
but we see them as our friends
and our families.

26:08.282 --> 26:10.117
[laughs]

26:10.117 --> 26:13.587
Do you even have a brain left
in that balding head of yours?

26:13.587 --> 26:14.488
Huh?

26:15.422 --> 26:16.090
Or is it just a bunch
of liberal bullshit

26:16.724 --> 26:18.259
floating around in oat milk?

26:18.259 --> 26:19.460
Come on, everybody.

26:20.461 --> 26:22.129
Let's get those nets ready
and save some lives.

26:22.129 --> 26:23.464
Hell yeah!

26:29.536 --> 26:31.605
♪

26:34.375 --> 26:37.378
You're still you.

26:37.378 --> 26:40.714
The virus hasn't erased you.

26:40.714 --> 26:42.650
Death hasn't erased you.

26:45.252 --> 26:47.254
But I have to be sure.

26:47.254 --> 26:48.522
I have to be.

26:48.522 --> 26:51.225
I have to be sure
you're still in there.

27:12.413 --> 27:13.547
[screaming]
Help! Help!

27:13.547 --> 27:14.381
Help me!

27:14.381 --> 27:15.649
[screaming]
Help me!

27:18.285 --> 27:19.353
[groans]

27:21.722 --> 27:23.390
Oh, geez.

27:24.491 --> 27:26.126
[exhales]

27:26.126 --> 27:28.429
Where the hell have you been?

27:29.763 --> 27:30.764
A fish finder.

27:30.764 --> 27:32.132
It's nowhere near as precise,

27:32.833 --> 27:33.434
but functionally
it's not that different

27:34.068 --> 27:35.169
from an ultrasound machine.

27:36.070 --> 27:36.270
It should give us a pretty
decent idea

27:37.104 --> 27:38.405
of the severity of
Mindy's condition.

27:39.240 --> 27:39.773
[scoffs]

27:39.773 --> 27:41.408
You're out of your mind.

27:42.142 --> 27:44.812
Yeah, well, at least
I'm doing something.

27:44.812 --> 27:47.548
She's getting worse.
Please help her.

27:48.282 --> 27:50.584
That's exactly what
I'm gonna do.

27:50.584 --> 27:52.253
All right, I'm gonna need
someone to hold her still.

27:52.253 --> 27:53.420
Where's Lauren?

27:54.521 --> 27:56.257
I sent her off to the pharmacy
to get pain medicine.

27:56.257 --> 27:59.126
I figured she'd know
what to look for.

27:59.126 --> 28:00.361
Herb.

28:01.462 --> 28:02.763
Jesus Christ, can you not be
an asshole for one minute?

28:04.064 --> 28:06.567
Hey, I'd rather be an asshole
than a naive little boy.

28:06.567 --> 28:08.836
You're so desperate
to impress your patients

28:08.836 --> 28:12.139
you can't even tell when you're
being scammed by a drug addict.

28:12.139 --> 28:13.274
But she saw.

28:13.274 --> 28:16.443
Lauren saw your weakness.

28:16.443 --> 28:19.813
She batted her eyelashes and
out comes your prescription pad.

28:19.813 --> 28:21.649
You didn't have to call
the police.

28:21.649 --> 28:24.218
She didn't have to go to jail.
We could have helped her.

28:24.218 --> 28:24.752
What's wrong?

28:24.752 --> 28:25.286
Hold her steady.

28:25.753 --> 28:26.153
What's happening?

28:26.954 --> 28:28.789
We need to get that stick out!
Now!

28:28.789 --> 28:29.723
Didn't swipe any, did you?

28:29.723 --> 28:31.225
Fuck you.

28:32.259 --> 28:33.193
Herb, what the hell?
Lauren, I need your help.

28:34.295 --> 28:36.096
It's okay. It's okay.

28:38.399 --> 28:41.368
Please! What are you doing?
Please, stop!

28:42.670 --> 28:44.138
Please, stop.

28:46.273 --> 28:48.609
Lauren, I need gauze, now!

28:49.310 --> 28:51.211
We need gauze!

28:51.211 --> 28:52.346
Yeah.

28:56.116 --> 28:57.184
[cries of pain]

28:59.153 --> 29:02.189
[screaming and gasping]

29:12.099 --> 29:13.367
[screaming]
Anybody!
Help! Help!!

29:14.542 --> 29:16.377
I've been trying to help you!
I'm trying‐

29:16.377 --> 29:18.847
Stop! Look, look, look!

29:54.315 --> 29:54.983
[loud growl]

29:57.886 --> 29:59.621
[snarling and growling]

30:09.864 --> 30:10.865
Dammit.

30:15.336 --> 30:16.337
Dammit!

30:35.990 --> 30:37.659
Hey, bub.

30:38.893 --> 30:38.927
McDermott: Don't forget,
if you get into trouble...

30:39.194 --> 30:39.394
Look.

30:40.094 --> 30:40.428
...just pass it to Luke.

30:41.362 --> 30:42.997
Cam: Mom, will you
make him stop.

30:44.365 --> 30:45.366
Don't post this.

30:46.468 --> 30:46.501
McDermott: Don't worry,
I won't share it.

30:47.101 --> 30:48.536
Cam: You better not.

30:54.509 --> 30:56.778
I knew it. I knew it.

30:56.778 --> 30:58.012
[loud growl]

30:59.714 --> 31:01.282
[snarling and growling]

31:08.556 --> 31:11.559
[roars]

31:15.597 --> 31:17.599
[roars]

31:30.512 --> 31:31.546
Hey.

31:32.847 --> 31:34.616
I'm so glad to see you.

31:38.453 --> 31:43.324
Have you... have you
been drinking?

31:43.324 --> 31:49.364
Uh... yeah, um... I mean...
I was talking to Trey Bowman,

31:49.364 --> 31:51.800
the mayor's husband and‐

31:51.800 --> 31:56.070
Amy, are you kidding me?

31:56.070 --> 31:57.772
I'm over here trying
to save people

31:57.772 --> 32:01.543
and you're having a...
a party?

32:01.543 --> 32:03.611
Okay, woah, we were
just talking.

32:03.611 --> 32:05.513
He's in a pretty dark place.

32:05.513 --> 32:06.881
Oh. He is?

32:10.785 --> 32:15.023
You know that woman we found
on the side of the road?

32:15.023 --> 32:17.992
The one with a branch
in her side?

32:19.661 --> 32:22.897
She's dead, Amy.

32:22.897 --> 32:24.399
Oh, god.

32:24.399 --> 32:27.735
I... that's...
that's awful, I...

32:30.605 --> 32:35.944
She was seizing and uh...
I had to do something.

32:39.781 --> 32:43.384
I really, really thought
I could save her.

32:43.384 --> 32:44.786
Okay.

32:44.786 --> 32:45.753
Don't blame yourself.

32:45.753 --> 32:48.056
Like, you can't save everybody.

32:48.056 --> 32:51.993
What kind of doctor would I be
if I didn't try, huh?

32:54.496 --> 32:57.899
Oh yeah, that's right.

32:57.899 --> 33:00.068
I'd be your dad.

33:00.068 --> 33:02.770
I can't believe I almost married
you today.

33:02.770 --> 33:05.740
What the hell is that supposed
to mean?

33:07.609 --> 33:10.645
Ever since we got engaged

33:10.645 --> 33:14.315
I felt like I wasn't good enough
for you.

33:14.315 --> 33:18.987
Like I wasn't good enough
to be a part of your family.

33:18.987 --> 33:25.627
But today, with your dad waving
that prenup in my face,

33:25.627 --> 33:31.332
I realized you don't think
I'm good enough.

33:31.332 --> 33:33.968
[teary]
Jai. I... Jai, please...

33:43.344 --> 33:46.581
You deserved better
than this.

33:46.581 --> 33:49.851
But shit's pretty
fucked up right now.

34:01.429 --> 34:04.365
[sobbing]
Why is this happening?

34:04.365 --> 34:06.668
[sobbing]

34:06.668 --> 34:09.337
Why us? Why here?

34:13.942 --> 34:18.012
I don't wanna die.
Not like this.

34:19.781 --> 34:25.353
[sobbing]

34:48.476 --> 34:51.312
Maybe you're one of
the lucky ones.

34:58.786 --> 35:03.725
[groans]

35:11.633 --> 35:13.334
[breathing heavily]

35:16.504 --> 35:18.006
There you are.

35:18.006 --> 35:20.642
Listen, we need to talk.

35:20.642 --> 35:22.043
I've been doing some thinking

35:22.043 --> 35:24.012
on the state of
our relationship...

35:25.713 --> 35:27.382
Oh man.

35:27.382 --> 35:28.750
You haven't dipped
since college.

35:28.750 --> 35:30.618
Trey, what do you want?

35:30.618 --> 35:31.619
The way you treat me?

35:31.619 --> 35:33.421
The way you take me
for granted?

35:33.421 --> 35:35.056
It isn't okay.

35:35.056 --> 35:36.758
I'm a person.

35:36.758 --> 35:38.726
I'm a man, Paula.

35:38.726 --> 35:41.396
You need to start treating me
like one.

35:46.367 --> 35:49.003
We are not doing this.

35:49.003 --> 35:51.039
We have no police force.

35:51.039 --> 35:52.407
No outside help.

35:52.407 --> 35:54.943
And that idiot,
Pops Parker,

35:54.943 --> 35:56.478
has managed to convince
everyone in here

35:56.478 --> 36:00.381
that those monsters are their
long lost family members.

36:00.381 --> 36:03.051
So now I have to convince
a store full of morons

36:03.051 --> 36:06.054
that those things
are actually dangerous!

36:06.054 --> 36:06.955
No!

36:06.955 --> 36:08.690
No!!

36:09.858 --> 36:12.060
It's always about you and your
problems and what you need.

36:12.060 --> 36:14.462
This is about us.

36:14.462 --> 36:17.031
We had a real marriage once

36:17.031 --> 36:19.901
and I'm gonna fight
to get that back.

36:19.901 --> 36:23.304
I am more than the guy
who holds your purse.

36:23.304 --> 36:28.643
I'm your goddamn husband and
this family is my Krav Maga.

36:28.643 --> 36:30.311
What are you even‐

36:43.491 --> 36:45.660
That tasted like absolute ass.

36:56.471 --> 36:57.705
[door closes]

37:07.882 --> 37:09.284
[gasps]

37:09.918 --> 37:10.952
Hey, sweetie.

37:10.952 --> 37:12.654
You know, you're not always
right all the time.

37:12.654 --> 37:14.455
You know that?

37:16.291 --> 37:21.496
I was right about that patient
and I am right about Jai.

37:21.496 --> 37:23.898
He's a nice kid, yeah.

37:23.898 --> 37:25.900
Might even make
a decent husband.

37:25.900 --> 37:31.005
But you deserve more than
nice and decent.

37:31.005 --> 37:33.007
I hoped you'd see that.

37:34.843 --> 37:39.614
My whole life I worshipped you.

37:39.614 --> 37:42.817
I wanted to be just like you.

37:42.817 --> 37:46.020
And you know what
the worst part is?

37:46.020 --> 37:47.989
I think I am.

37:50.525 --> 37:51.593
Amy.

37:52.026 --> 37:53.328
Amy!

38:11.183 --> 38:19.263
[crying]
She wasn't just my sister,
she was my best friend.
We lived together, we went
birding together,

38:19.263 --> 38:25.136
and after mother died
we only had each other.

38:25.136 --> 38:28.270
[crying]
Now who do I have?

38:28.270 --> 38:31.306
Oh, no, no.
You have us.

38:31.306 --> 38:33.842
We're not just your neighbors,
Cindy.

38:33.842 --> 38:35.410
We're your family.

38:37.979 --> 38:40.782
We look after each other.

38:40.782 --> 38:43.184
We take care of each other,

38:43.184 --> 38:47.122
and that's exactly
what we're gonna do today.

38:49.858 --> 38:51.526
Have you seen Jai?

38:51.526 --> 38:54.062
Not for a while.

38:54.062 --> 38:55.563
Can you believe this guy?

38:55.563 --> 38:57.232
It's the damn apocalypse and
he's still running for mayor.

38:57.232 --> 38:58.500
It's up to us
right here and now

38:58.500 --> 39:01.403
to decide what kind of town
we want to be.

39:01.403 --> 39:04.506
A town that rules
with fear and violence,

39:04.506 --> 39:07.876
or a town that leads with
strength and compassion?

39:07.876 --> 39:10.946
Let us not go out there
and kill those people.

39:10.946 --> 39:14.382
Let us go out there
and save them.

39:14.382 --> 39:17.485
[applause]

39:19.254 --> 39:20.822
[screaming]

39:21.156 --> 39:22.157
Mindy!

39:22.457 --> 39:24.292
Is that you?

39:24.292 --> 39:25.427
She's one of them things.

39:25.427 --> 39:26.828
Oh shit.

39:28.496 --> 39:29.197
Oh no, no, no.

39:29.197 --> 39:30.498
It's okay, it's okay.

39:31.499 --> 39:33.101
No, no, no, no, no.
It's... it's... it's okay.

39:34.135 --> 39:36.504
We don't want to hurt you,
it's... it's just um...

39:36.504 --> 39:40.342
that's right,
you... you are fine.

39:40.342 --> 39:44.079
You are our friend.

39:44.079 --> 39:45.380
You see?

39:45.380 --> 39:46.948
They can be saved.

39:46.948 --> 39:47.949
[chuckles]

39:49.384 --> 39:50.819
[snarling]

39:50.819 --> 39:53.455
Get it off me!
Get it off me!!

39:53.455 --> 39:54.923
Somebody help me!

39:54.923 --> 39:55.824
[growling and snarling]

39:56.791 --> 39:57.058
Get a gun and shoot
this fucking thing!

39:57.058 --> 39:57.525
No!

39:57.525 --> 39:59.861
Kill it!

40:00.862 --> 40:02.264
Everybody, stand back!

40:02.264 --> 40:05.066
[battle cry]

40:05.066 --> 40:06.534
Get off of him!

40:06.534 --> 40:10.005
♪

40:10.005 --> 40:11.106
[thud]

40:11.106 --> 40:12.807
Trey, get outta there!

40:12.807 --> 40:16.411
[thuds]

40:23.018 --> 40:25.053
It's okay, Paula.

40:25.053 --> 40:26.888
I got this one.

40:26.888 --> 40:27.489
[gasps]

40:29.124 --> 40:30.458
Move!

40:30.458 --> 40:31.426
Move!

40:32.260 --> 40:33.495
Get off!

40:37.432 --> 40:39.100
[snarling and growling]

40:39.100 --> 40:41.069
[screaming]

40:56.851 --> 40:58.820
[gunshot]

40:59.854 --> 41:03.959
[gunshots]

41:04.526 --> 41:06.494
What the hell was that?

41:07.128 --> 41:08.129
[gunshot]

41:09.364 --> 41:10.365
[gunshot]

41:14.369 --> 41:15.403
Oh!

41:17.005 --> 41:18.373
[sobbing]
Oh, Trey.

41:20.442 --> 41:23.011
Did I get her?

41:23.011 --> 41:24.346
Yeah.

41:24.346 --> 41:26.381
Yeah, you got her.

41:26.381 --> 41:27.882
You saved us.

41:29.284 --> 41:31.019
You're a hero.

41:35.256 --> 41:36.558
[groan]

41:36.558 --> 41:40.028
[sobbing]

41:40.028 --> 41:42.297
Tr... Trey...

41:42.297 --> 41:45.233
[sobbing]

41:51.873 --> 41:54.409
Where the hell
did she come from?

